column2: Did you go on any rides this week?

column17: Went through plano. Very strong headwind on the ride back
column27: Pace was a little too fast for me, considering the wind we were facing. Longest t4k ride of mine so far
column32: First ride on back to back days. Went from Flower Mound High school to argyle texas through some gorgeous rural country roads! Very windy
It was a bit ambitious to dive into the 45 mile Out East route, especially during very windy conditions, but I was proud of all the hard work everyone put in to finish the ride.

column12: We rode River Legacy trials in Arlington, Tx. It went really well!

column37: We rode in San Antonio on Leon Creek Greenway. It was about 13 miles from the beginning to the end of the trail and back. I'm personally concerned about balance at  standstill, which is what caused my 1 fall and almost a second, but I am thinking/hoping it will get better with practice. I'm also concerned about sharp turns and biking in a narrow space, which I also hope will improve with practice.

column17: We did a ride out in Plano.
column32: This ride was REALLY hard on me. We went on back roads from Flower mound to Argyle. There were winds of between 20-30mph with lots of hills. The boys were great at being patient and waiting on me when I was struggling though.

column21: Kevin Helgren, Patrick x 2, Jordan Kohler, Jocelyn
column22: I lead the ride and took us down rio grande to town lake and then took the lance Armstrong bikeway around to austin high and then took a few hike and bike trails through tunnels and over bridges. Then we went down lake austin blvd and went through tarry town and up exposition - which has some great hills

column12: Shoal Creek into northwest Austin. Struggled on a few hills but just getting back into the breathing pattern.
column27: East Austin. Lots of hills which were good for me to challenge myself on following through on them. Finally learning how to enter hills with high cadence during this ride

column22: Fun ride -- we decided to do some exploring. Said exploration included hidden bike trails, dark tunnels, and the like. ;)
column31: Sunshine Garrison, Anthony McCoy, Stefanie Schultz, Vaibhav Bhamidipati
column32: This was hands-down the most challenging ride I've been on to-date. Not only did it near 50 miles in distance, but the wind was terrible. We did the 50-mile loop on Out East spontaneously, and I'm so happy we did. Challenging, sure, but no one said that biking to Alaska was going to be easy. Very rewarding ride with wonderful people!

column7: We started our ride at Shoral Creek. It was Laura's first ride and everything went really well.
column36: Christina Ibarra, Jacob Schmelz, Nichele Newman
column37: Rode in San Antonio Leon Green Trails, super windy, and cold.

column7: This was my first ride so I was a little nervous but it went really well! Kitty was really patient and helpful.

column12: A nice ride! We talked a lot of the way for the first 10 miles then the last 10 we rode faster!

column17: We rode in Houston. Route was pretty flat and drivers were rude. But, wonderful ride.
column37: Extremely windy and we rode 360. It was Shelly's second ride and she did great.

column27: 360 access road loop in Hurst, TX

column37: Rode in a greenway in San Antonio

column17: I kicked madi's butt through the whole ride and went about a 17mph pace but had to stop for her, which is why my pace is 15. (Lolz this is Madi and Raveena is in panama so I am entering her ride info for her, but she really did kick my ass).

column27: Awesome ride out east. Lots of wind which made the hills even more challenging! We made one extended stop after 25 miles to eat some snacks. It was great to ride for a longer amount of time at once!

column32: We did the 50 mi route out east! SOoooOoOo windy!

We went Out East! It was beautiful! But WINDY!!!! There were a lot of hills. Those will be the death of me. Anthony was a great sweep and helped me catch up when I needed it. But I kept going all the way :) It had been a while since I had been on my bike. It felt good! It was a good challenge. We all felt accomplished afterwards :)

column17: We went on a ride in Dallas with a couple hills in a loop. Felt pretty good about the ride.
column31: Sunshine, Kevin Helgren, Anthony, and Stephanie
column32: We went on what was supposed to be just the Far East route in Austin and ended up deciding to try and aim for 50 miles instead. It was super windy and the extra distance we added was almost completely uphill as well. I felt exhausted by the end of it but also really accomplished.

column37:
